{
  "page": "Pypar",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\"><img alt=\"Night&#39;s Watch.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/50px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/75px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/100px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Pypar</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\"><img alt=\"Night&#39;s Watch.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/50px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/75px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/Night%27s_Watch.svg/100px-Night%27s_Watch.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Pypar.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Pypar.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8f/Pypar.jpg/350px-Pypar.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"538\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8f/Pypar.jpg/525px-Pypar.jpg 1.5x, /images/8/8f/Pypar.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Pypar by Amok</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Pyp</li><li>Monkey<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Mummer's Monkey<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafpypar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafpypar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/List_of_actors_of_the_televised_series#Jozef_Altin.2CPypar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"List of actors of the televised series\">Jozef Altin</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <br /><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_1\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 1\">Season 1</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_3\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 3\">3</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_4\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 4\">4</a></td></tr></tbody></table> \n<p><b>Pypar</b>, commonly known as <b>Pyp</b>, is a member of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>. He is in the same recruit class as <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>.\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>, Pypar is portrayed by Jozef Altin.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Pypar\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Pypar</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Pypar\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Pypar</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Pypar\" title=\"Category:Images of Pypar\">Images of Pypar</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Pypar is small and has large ears<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> which he can wiggle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Claiming to be able to identify a person's origin by their accent,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Pyp can imitate a hundred different voices and loves to act.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> He can whistle extremely loudly and shrilly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pypar enjoys teasing his friend, <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> thinks Pyp has stupid japes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos75.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos75.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Before coming to the Wall, Pypar had traveled the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> with a <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummers</a>' troupe.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Pypar is part of the same <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow%27s_Night%27s_Watch_recruitment_group\" title=\"Jon Snow&#39;s Night&#39;s Watch recruitment group\">group of recuits</a> to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>. During sword practice, Jon thinks Pyp uses his sword like a dagger.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> After seeing Jon helping <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a>, Pyp asks Jon for help; Pyp then does not drop his sword as often as he once did.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Alliser_Thorne\" title=\"Alliser Thorne\">Alliser Thorne</a> picks on <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> when he arrives at the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, commanding <a href=\"/index.php/Halder\" title=\"Halder\">Halder</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rast\" title=\"Rast\">Rast</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Albett\" title=\"Albett\">Albett</a> to fight the inept youth. Grenn, Jon, and Pyp defend Sam, however. Because Rast is still willing to hurt Sam for Alliser, he is visited in the night by Pyp, Grenn, and Jon and threatened by Jon's <a href=\"/index.php/Direwolf\" title=\"Direwolf\">direwolf</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ghost\" title=\"Ghost\">Ghost</a>. Sam joins Pyp, Jon, Grenn and Halder during meals and eventually shares in their jests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyp is derisively nicknamed \"<a href=\"/index.php/Monkey\" title=\"Monkey\">Monkey</a>\" and \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">Mummer</a>'s Monkey\" by Alliser.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Pyp is named to the <a href=\"/index.php/Ranger\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ranger\">rangers</a> when Alliser believes him ready to man the Wall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyp informs Jon that King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a> has died. When Alliser calls Jon a traitor's bastard after <a href=\"/index.php/Arrest_of_Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Arrest of Eddard Stark\">the arrest</a> of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, Jon's father, Pyp tries to stop Jon from attacking the master-at-arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jon saves the life of <a href=\"/index.php/Jeor_Mormont\" title=\"Jeor Mormont\">Jeor Mormont</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, when he is attacked by <a href=\"/index.php/Othor\" title=\"Othor\">a wight</a>. Out of gratitude, the Old Bear gives Jon his family sword, <a href=\"/index.php/Longclaw\" title=\"Longclaw\">Longclaw</a>, as a gift. Afterwards, Pyp joins others who ask Jon to show them the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> blade, as they knew about the present before Jon did.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>     \n</p><p>Pyp is among the group of friends who stop Jon from abandoning the Night's Watch and forswearing himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Although Pyp and <a href=\"/index.php/Todder\" title=\"Todder\">Todder</a> want to participate in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_ranging\" title=\"Great ranging\">great ranging</a> venturing <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>, they remain at <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a>. Before Grenn leaves with the ranging, Pyp, Toad, and Halder bring him to <a href=\"/index.php/Mole%27s_Town\" title=\"Mole&#39;s Town\">Mole's Town</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/aa/Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg/350px-Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"266\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/aa/Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg/525px-Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/aa/Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg/700px-Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Castle_Black_Squad_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Dolorous Edd</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>, Pyp, <a href=\"/index.php/Satin\" title=\"Satin\">Satin</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a>, by chillyravenart ©</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Bowen_Marsh\" title=\"Bowen Marsh\">Bowen Marsh</a> leaves Pypar behind for being too small and inexperienced when he departs <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a> to deal with <a href=\"/index.php/Wildling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildling\">wildling</a> attacks along the Wall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyp's friend <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a> is among a dozen who reach Castle Black after the <a href=\"/index.php/Mutiny_at_Craster%27s_Keep\" title=\"Mutiny at Craster&#39;s Keep\">mutiny at Craster's Keep</a>. When <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> returns to the Wall, he is informed by Pyp, Grenn, and Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a> about the <a href=\"/index.php/Capture_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Capture of Winterfell\">supposed deaths</a> of his half brothers, <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> Pyp helps villagers from <a href=\"/index.php/Mole%27s_Town\" title=\"Mole&#39;s Town\">Mole's Town</a> seek shelter atop the Wall prior to the <a href=\"/index.php/Attack_on_Castle_Black\" title=\"Attack on Castle Black\">attack on Castle Black</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyp is one of the many fighters atop the Wall when <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a>'s army assaults the Watch in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">battle beneath the Wall</a>. He lights a dozen jars of lamp oil on fire before they are dropped on the wildlings below, with the Watch then pouring pitch on the attackers. Pyp, Grenn, and <a href=\"/index.php/Kegs\" title=\"Kegs\">Kegs</a> force away <a href=\"/index.php/Mammoths\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mammoths\">mammoths</a> by dropping barrels of burning oil from above. Pyp retches when he sees the bodies of <a href=\"/index.php/Donal_Noye\" title=\"Donal Noye\">Donal Noye</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Mag_Mar_Tun_Doh_Weg\" title=\"Mag Mar Tun Doh Weg\">Mag Mar Tun Doh Weg</a> at the gate through the Wall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> Pyp refers to arrows shot by wildlings in the morning as \"breakfast arrows\", and he names straw scarecrows after members of the Night's Watch. Jon tasks Pyp with commanding the Wall when he descends to Castle Black at one point during the siege.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyp greets Sam warmly when he returns to Castle Black, whooping loudly. During the Night's Watch <a href=\"/index.php/Election\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Election\">election</a>, Pyp votes for <a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Eddison Tollett</a>, a jape that Sam thinks is stupid. In conversation with Pyp and Grenn, Sam starts to think that one of the leading candidates in the election should withdraw to support the other, and Pyp notes that Sam would be the best one to talk to them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos75.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos75.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> During the election, when Jon Snow's name is put forward as a candidate by Dolorous Edd, Jon initially thinks it must be one of Pyp's japes. When Jon is elected the new <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, Pyp is among those who congratulate him. Pyp also congratulates Sam for managing to get Jon elected, calling him a wizard and a wonder and a marvel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Pypar and Grenn practice with longbows. Pyp becomes resentful towards Jon, the new <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, because Jon turns distant, avoiding the friends who aided his rise to power.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Pyp reports that <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> intends to burn <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> because of his king's blood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Jon sees Pyp eating with Grenn and his other friends in the cellar below the armory. When Pyp makes jests about the rituals of <a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">R'hllor</a>, Jon orders him to stop, grateful none of the <a href=\"/index.php/Queen%27s_men\" title=\"Queen&#39;s men\">queen's men</a> heard the japes. Afterward, Lord Commander Snow reluctantly assigns Pyp and Grenn to <a href=\"/index.php/Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\" title=\"Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\">Eastwatch-by-the-Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Pypar\">Quotes by Pypar</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Pypar\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c5/Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png/350px-Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"433\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c5/Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png/525px-Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c5/Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png/700px-Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pypar_by_Lu_Potter.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Pypar, by Lu Potter ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Samwell</b>: I ... if you want, you can call me Sam. My mother calls me Sam.<br />\n</p><p><b>Pypar</b>: You can call him Lord Snow. You don't want to know what his mother calls him.<br />\n<b>Jon</b>: These two are Grenn and Pypar.<br />\n<b>Pypar</b>: Grenn's the ugly one.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Grenn</b>: You're uglier than me. At least I don't have ears like a <a href=\"/index.php/Bat\" title=\"Bat\">bat</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a>, Pypar, <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Pypar</b>: So here are your choices. Kill me, or come back with me.<br />\n<b>Jon</b>: Damn you. Damn you all.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Pypar and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Turtle_(siege_engine)\" title=\"Turtle (siege engine)\">turtle</a> was stuffed full of rabbits! Look at them hop away!<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Pypar during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">battle beneath the Wall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jon</b>: You’re all a bunch of mad fools, do you know that?<br />\n<b>Pypar</b>: Us? You call <i>us</i> fools? We’re not the ones who got <a href=\"/index.php/Elections\" title=\"Elections\">chosen</a> as the nine-hundredth-and-ninety-eighth <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%E2%80%99s_Watch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night’s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night’s Watch</a>. You best have some <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>, Lord Jon. I think you’re going to need a <i>lot</i> of wine.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos79.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> and Pypar</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Pypar</b>: The night is dark and full of turnips. Let us all pray for venison, my children, with some onions and a bit of tasty gravy.<br />\n</p><p><b>Jon</b>: Making mock of another man's prayer is fool's work, Pyp. And dangerous.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Pypar</b>: If the <a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">red god's</a> offended, let him strike me down.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Pypar and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Pypar\">Quotes about Pypar</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Pypar\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummer</a>'s boy with the big ears was a born liar with a hundred different voices, and he did not tell his tales so much as live them, playing all the parts as needed, a king one moment and a swineherd the next. When he turned into an <a href=\"/index.php/Ale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ale\">alehouse</a> girl or a virgin princess, he used a high falsetto voice that reduced them all to tears of helpless laughter, and his eunuchs were always eerily accurate caricatures of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Alliser_Thorne\" title=\"Alliser Thorne\">Alliser</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>They will call you men of <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> now, but you are bigger fools than the Mummer's Monkey here if you believe that. You are boys still, green and stinking of summer, and when the winter comes you will die like flies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Alliser_Thorne\" title=\"Alliser Thorne\">Alliser Thorne</a> to Pyp's fellow recruits</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I am the shield that guards the realms of men, he remembered. He wondered what those men would say if they realized <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">their realms</a> were being guarded by the likes of <a href=\"/index.php/Grenn\" title=\"Grenn\">Grenn</a>, Pyp, and <a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Dolorous Edd</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pypar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <